---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Planning & Evaluation"
  description="IC&RC Prevention Specialist Domain 1. Needs-assessment templates, logic models, and evaluation tools for problem gambling prevention plans."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">
        <a href="/professionals">← For prevention professionals</a> · IC&amp;RC PS Domain 1
      </p>
      <h1>Planning &amp; Evaluation</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Tools to assess need, plan programming, and measure what works — the
        backbone of an evidence-based problem gambling prevention plan.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>What this domain covers</h2>
      <p>
        Planning and evaluation is about using data to decide where to focus,
        designing programming that follows from that data, and measuring outcomes
        so you can show impact and improve. It maps directly to the Assessment,
        Planning, and Evaluation steps of SAMHSA's Strategic Prevention Framework.
      </p>
      <h2>Resources here (filling in)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Needs-assessment templates for problem gambling</li>
        <li>Logic-model worksheets</li>
        <li>Evaluation rubrics for state PG prevention plans</li>
        <li>State-by-state regulatory and resource data you can cite in assessments</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Downloadable templates are being added. In the meantime, the
        <a href="/methodology">methodology &amp; data sources</a> page documents the
        citable data behind every state page. All resources are free; no login is
        required.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
